tldr: The user requested to implement a database, admin dashboard, and
  authentication for a sleep questionnaire application based on an SOW. I
  evaluated the codebase, created a plan, implemented the features including a
  simplified middleware-based authentication, and guided the user through
  database setup and initial testing.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database functionality, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication. After evaluating the existing codebase, I developed a plan to
  implement a  model in Prisma for a PostgreSQL database
  (NeonDB), create API endpoints for data submission, retrieval, and CSV export,
  and build a basic admin dashboard. Authentication was a key component,
  initially implemented with custom session management, but later refined to
  leverage Next.js middleware for a simpler, more efficient route protection
  mechanism using a basic password-protected cookie. I provided comprehensive
  instructions for database setup and guided the user through testing the new
  features, including submitting a questionnaire, logging into the admin
  dashboard, and attempting a CSV download. The testing phase revealed that the
  "Pre-fill & Jump to Report" button did not trigger the database save,
  prompting a plan to properly submit the form.
